==Work==
Strachan's work has been published in ''[[New Writing]]'' 15, ''[[Bordercrossing Berlin]]'', ''[[The Edinburgh Companion to Contemporary Scottish Literature]]'' and ''[[The Antigonish Review]]''.<ref name="UG" /> In 2006 she was named the first writer-in-residence at the [[National Museum of Scotland]] in [[Edinburgh]].<ref>{{Cite news
  | last = Mather
  | first = Adrian
  | author-link =
  | title = Zoe books in at museum to tell her story from history
  | newspaper = [[The Scotsman]]
  | pages =
  | year =
  | date = 2006-10-09
  | url =http://news.scotsman.com/literacyinscotland/Zoe-books-in-at-museum.2817193.jp
  | accessdate =2009-06-02
  | postscript = . }}
</ref> Her first novel, ''Negative Space'', was published in 2002 by [[Picador (imprint)|Picador]].<ref name="OS">{{Cite web
  | last = Strachan
  | first = Zo<U+00EB>
  | authorlink =
  | coauthors =
  | title = Zo<U+00EB> Strachan
  | work = Official site
  | publisher =
  | date =
  | url = http://zoestrachan.com/
  | format =
  | doi =
  | accessdate =2009-06-02 }}
</ref> It won the [[Betty Trask Award]] in 2003 and was short-listed for the Saltire First Book of the Year Award.<ref name="UG" /> Her second novel was 2004's ''Spin Cycle''. In 2008 Strachan was awarded the [[Hermann Kesten]] Stipendium fellowship.<ref name="list" /> As of June 2009, she was working on her third  novel, ''Play Dead''.<ref name="OS" />

